The paper focuses on large scale image retrieval, which is a task related to computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The proposed model is a deep learning model that learns the quantization codes sequentially, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The model is evaluated on benchmark datasets, which is a common practice in multimedia (cs.MM) and natural language processing (cs.CL) research.
